From 4af780f7bd480019cc8a1da9c7c9facedf95f044 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Airey <aireypaul@googlemail.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Apr 2026 21:37:28 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] feat: bring Outlook + Yahoo/IMAP email scanning to full Gmail
 parity

Outlook scanner: complete rewrite with 7 parallel KQL search queries,
full HTML body extraction, Claude Sonnet analysis with comprehensive
UK consumer law prompt, and 4-table database persistence (tasks,
subscriptions, money_hub_alerts, scanned_receipts).

IMAP scanner (Yahoo/Other): increased body extraction from 200 to
2000 chars, added plan/rate limit checks, admin bypass, maxDuration
120, 4-table persistence matching Gmail/Outlook standard.

Scanner UI: Yahoo button enters IMAP mode correctly, "Other" provider
now shows custom host/port fields for unmapped email domains, all
modal states properly reset on close.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
